```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Perform an initial experiment using dataset exemplars to observe the neuron's typical behavior on real images 
    activation_list, image_list = tools.dataset_exemplars(system)
    # Document the experiment results
    prompt_list = ['dataset_exemplar_' + str(i) for i in range(len(image_list))] # Create prompt list to match the number of images
    summarization = tools.summarize_images(image_list) # Summarize to get a better understanding of what common theme might be activating the neuron
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, image_list, prompt_list, summarization)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test if the neuron is selective for domed architectural structures versus other types of buildings
    prompts = ["a modern skyscraper", "a traditional domed building", "a flat-roofed house"]
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
    
    # Test if the neuron is selective for the curve shape regardless of context
    prompts = ["a spherical object on a blank background", 
               "a curved banana on a table",
               "a person wearing a helmet with a round top"]
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
    
    # Test for contrast between sky and curved silhouette selectivity
    # Generate images of domed buildings at different times of day to change the sky/background contrast
    prompts = ["a domed building at sunset", 
               "a domed building at night under a full moon", 
               "a domed building against a bright blue sky"]
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Conduct further experiments to confirm the neuron's selectivity for domed architectural structures by testing with different types of domes and varying contexts to see if there is a specific aspect of the domes (e.g. material, color, style) that the neuron is responsive to.
    prompts = ["a glass-domed conservatory", 
               "a metal-domed sports arena", 
               "a stone-domed ancient temple"]
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
    
    # Additionally, test if the neuron is selective for the interior of domed structures as well, which also have a similar curved shape
    prompts = ["interior of a glass-domed conservatory", 
               "interior of a metal-domed sports arena", 
               "interior of a stone-domed ancient temple"]
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
```
